cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR

This paper focuses on the security and trustworthiness of Chinese Android app markets, which suggests a strong connection to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves analyzing the publishing dynamics and developer behavior of these app markets, which could fall under the cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories. The prevalence of misbehavior in the app markets could also relate to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the study involves analyzing a large dataset of Android apps, which could fall under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
